<span id="freeTextContainer1639343635279581664">This book of essays is worth a read and made me think in new ways. Specifically, I saw a black conservatism I didn&apos;t know about before (from people I side-eye like Bill Cosby to people I admire like Barack Obama). My favorite essay by far is &quot;Why Do So Few Blacks Study the Civil War?&quot; for its insight on revising and reframing history. Coates is skeptical and thoughtful.</span>
  <span id="freeText1639343635279581664" style="display:none">This book of essays is worth a read and made me think in new ways. Specifically, I saw a black conservatism I didn't know about before (from people I side-eye like Bill Cosby to people I admire like Barack Obama). My favorite essay by far is "Why Do So Few Blacks Study the Civil War?" for its insight on revising and reframing history. Coates is skeptical and thoughtful.</span>
